    "short_description": {
        "value": "FlexiMo is a flexible remote sensing foundation model that enables adaptation to arbitrary spatial resolutions, patch sizes, and channel counts. It features a spatial resolution-aware module using parameter-free alignment embedding and a lightweight channel adaptation module leveraging prior spectral information from sensors. FlexiMo achieves strong generalization and robustness across diverse multimodal, multi-resolution, and multi-scale datasets for tasks such as scene classification, land cover classification, building segmentation, and cloud detection.",
